Alright, get ready for a review that'll make your mouth water and your fingers itch to make a reservation!
Listen up, fellow foodies and romance seekers! My recent expedition to Tonic Seafood & Steak in Wilmington was nothing short of spectacular. Picture this: a balmy evening, stars peeking out, and my amazing girlfriend by my side as we dined al fresco in an atmosphere that whispered sweet nothings.
Let's talk food, shall we? I dove headfirst into the duck, and oh boy, the flavor was an absolute symphony! My girlfriend, meanwhile, was in pure bliss with her crab cake. Seriously, every bite was a testament to culinary artistry. And the drinks? Forget about it! They were so good, they practically danced on our tongues.
Now, let's give a standing ovation to the service. Our waiter was a true maestro! Not only was he a wizard with the extensive whiskey, bourbon, and scotch selections, but he even concocted a custom cocktail for my girlfriend that was spot-on! Talk about going the extra mile!
We kicked things off with the calamari and beef short rib egg rolls ‚Äì a delightful duet of textures and tastes that set the stage for the main event. Yes, it's a tad on the pricier side, but trust me on this one, every single penny was an investment in an unforgettable experience.
Fast forward, and I've already played restaurant matchmaker, recommending Tonic to one of my best friends. Guess what? They were absolutely blown away and showered me with gratitude for the tip!
So, if you're looking for a top-notch dining experience in Wilmington, a place that nails the food, the drinks, the service, and sets the perfect romantic mood, then Tonic Seafood & Steak is your spot. Trust me, your taste buds (and your date!) will thank you. I'm already counting down the days until my next visit!

Went here for dinner during happy hour and had a great time! We ordered the brussels sprouts, fried calamari, and wings, all were tasty and hit the spot. Fun atmosphere, good deals on drinks, and good food. Would definitely go again!

I've been here before, but I recently went back to see if there was a change. I'm not sure if I will be coming back again. I wasn't crazy about the drinks I got or the selections. The appetizers were just okay, and so was the Fillet steak. The presentation was not so good. Wasn't blown away. For the price of the bill, I wasn't satisfied. The atmosphere for a Friday night was very quiet. Service was very good, tho.

Alex K was five star the most amazing waiteress she checked on us constantly. She make sure everybody was having a good time. Our meals were exquisite the steak melted in our mouth. We celebrated three birthdays and one shot she took photos. She was so awesome. The best waitress ever ever ever if you‚Äôre gonna come, Titanic ask for Alex K there‚Äôs three of them Alex K good times thanks Alex you were amazing once again.

editorial_summary.overview: Creative, modern seafood dishes in a spacious eatery with a large wine selection & convivial bar.
